DOCUMENT();       

loadMacros("PG.pl",
           "PGbasicmacros.pl",
           "PGchoicemacros.pl",
           "PGanswermacros.pl",
           "PGgraphmacros.pl",
           "PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl",
           "PGgraphmacros.pl"
           );
       
TEXT(beginproblem()); # standard preamble to each problem.


$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$y1_th = random(8,12,1);
$y1 = $y1_th*1000+500;
$tick = random(115,139,2);
$ans = "$tick*n - $y1";

BEGIN_TEXT
Question 27:
$BR $SPACE $BR
A flight costs ${DOLLAR}$y1_th,500 to operate, regardless of the number of passengers.  Each ticket costs ${DOLLAR}$tick.  Express profit, $BITALIC P${EITALIC}, as a linear function of the number of passengers, $BITALIC n${EITALIC}, on the flight.  
$BR $SPACE $BR
\( P = \ \) \{ ans_rule(20) \} (do not enter commas in your formula)
END_TEXT

ANS(fun_cmp($ans,vars=>'n'));

SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$BR $SPACE $BR
$BBOLD SOLUTION $EBOLD
$BR
The profit, $BITALIC P${EITALIC}, is the difference between the revenue and the expenses.  The expenses are ${DOLLAR}$y1_th,500 and do not depend on $BITALIC n${EITALIC}, the number of passengers on the plane.  The revenue equals the cost per ticket times the number of tickets bought (or the number of passengers on the plane).  Therefore we have
$BR $SPACE $BR
$SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE 
\( P = \mbox{Revenue} - \mbox{Expense} = ( $tick n ) - ( $y1 ) = $tick n - $y1 \) 
$BR
END_SOLUTION
ENDDOCUMENT();   # This should be the last executable line in the problem.